[32m+[m[32m## Benefits Achieved[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m### üîÑ **Continuous Backup**[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Every bitmap discovery is immediately committed to Git[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Complete history of all data additions with timestamps[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- No risk of data loss between manual commits[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m### üç¥ **Fork-Friendly Repository**[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Anyone forking the repository gets up-to-date CSV data[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Forks can continue tracking from the latest state[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Eliminates need to manually sync data files[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m### üìä **Version Control Integration**[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Each bitmap discovery creates a Git commit with block number[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Easy to track when specific bitmaps were discovered[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Rollback capabilities for data recovery[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m### ü§ù **Collaborative Development**[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Multiple instances can sync via Git remotes[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Team members can contribute without data conflicts[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m- Transparent change tracking for all participants[m[41m[m
